body:
`Part of #9264 keycard sign-in epic (mark as checked there, when closing this issue)`
There are several layout issues on the sign in screens:


**General comment:**
_Please take all the values (margins, heights, width from Figma. If something seems wrong or inconsistent, please, leave a comment in Figma or here)_

**Step 1.**
- The "Access key" button should be in a footer with a 1px top border. This footer should stick to the bottom regardless of the size of the device screen;
- On smaller screens, the footer (with the "Access key" button inside) and the num pad should shrink according to the spec below. Numpad on all screens is floated to the bottom, not centered;
- On smaller screens the num pad is resized according to the spec below;
- The bottom margin in the footer if for iOS devices with a virtual keyboard only;

<img width="826" alt="st1" src="https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3115606/67829927-d0f24700-fb13-11e9-9f90-0fc6789fe8c5.png">

<img width="1492" alt="step1" src="https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3115606/67829934-d5b6fb00-fb13-11e9-8f73-9dcd85b7d1dd.png">

**Step 2.**
- The NFC <-> Phone image should be replaced with the one below (Exported: [Big](https://www.dropbox.com/s/bvjnuc1n294bo9t/nfc-phone%404x.png?dl=0), [Small](https://www.dropbox.com/s/v7bapijc5khvhfm/nfc-phone-small%404x.png?dl=0). Or export from Figma directly );
- This image also floats to the bottom, it's not centered or scaled. On smaller screens it's replaced (not just scaled) with another image;
- `Step 1 of 2` and `Hold card to the back of your phone` text is resized on smaller screens according to spec below;

<img width="850" alt="st2" src="https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3115606/67829966-f1ba9c80-fb13-11e9-905e-985b8c3aca43.png">

<img width="1350" alt="step2" src="https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3115606/67829982-04cd6c80-fb14-11e9-97b3-573aca04c817.png">


